# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Overview
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Stack'd Fries Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package (latest version)
- Package manager: npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with new dependency tree

### 2. Code Integration
**Modified: `src/app/layout.tsx`**
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next';`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the body, placed after the existing `<Analytics />` component
- Implementation follows Next.js App Router best practices as documented in the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router (v13.5+):
- Used the Next.js-specific import path: `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
- Placed the component at the root layout level to track all pages
- Positioned alongside the existing Vercel Analytics component for consistent monitoring setup

## Verification

✅ **Build Status:** Successfully built with no errors
- Command: `npm run build`
- Result: Production build completed successfully

✅ **Linting:** No new linting errors introduced
- Command: `npm run lint`
- Result: Pre-existing linting warnings in other files remain unchanged; no errors related to Speed Insights changes

## Files Modified
1. `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
2. `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package dependencies
3. `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component

## Next Steps
Upon deployment to Vercel, Speed Insights will automatically activate and begin collecting performance metrics from user visits. No additional configuration is required.
